<<<api>>>: Iterator.next
<<<code>>>: Set<String> windowsid = driver.getWindowHandles();
Iterator<String> iterate = windowsid.iterator();
String mainwindow_id = iterate.next();
String tabbedwindow_id = iterate.next();
while(iterate.hasNext()){
    System.out.println(iterate.next());
}
<<<explanation>>>: The error "java.util.NoSuchElementException" occurs when you try to call the next() method on an iterator that has no more elements. In your code, you are calling iterate.next() twice before checking if there are more elements using iterate.hasNext(). To fix this, move the iteration loop after retrieving the mainwindow_id and tabbedwindow_id.
